claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A table showing the incidence and severity of solicited adverse events (fever, fatigue/lack of energy, shivering/chills, arthralgia/joint pain, myalgia/muscle pain, headache, nausea, malaise, vomiting) in study subjects across different treatment arms. does not support the claim: the table only presents adverse event data and contains no information on vaccine production methods, mutations during production, or any impact on effectiveness. Note: Only safety data are shown; production and mutation information is not present in the image.
